{"id":"palsy","term":"Palsy","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A shorter form of “paralysis.” Many persons thus afflicted were cured by our Lord (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 4:24\">Matt. 4:24</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 8:5\">8:5-13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 9:2\">9:2-7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Mark 2:3\">Mark 2:3-11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 7:2\">Luke 7:2-10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 5:5\">John 5:5-7</a>) and the apostles (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 8:7\">Acts 8:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 9:33\">9:33</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 9:34\">34</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Matthew 4:24","Matthew 8:5","Matthew 9:2","Mark 2:3","Luke 7:2","John 5:5","Acts 8:7","Acts 9:33","Acts 9:34"]}